newsitem.title: PAKISTAN: Pakistan money rates end up despite funds inflow.
newsitem.headline: Pakistan money rates end up despite funds inflow.

text.p: Pakistan's inter-bank money rates stayed high on Wednesday despite an inflow of about 1.6 billion rupees on maturity of federal investment bonds and T-bills, dealers said.

They said rates were likely to remain firm on Thursday as no major inflow was expected. The market remained sluggish and overnight funds were traded at 17 percent as the inflows could not offset the liquidity shortage, one dealer said.
The inflows reduced the amount discounted to about five billion rupees from 6.5 billion rupees on Tuesday, he said.
